This paper is primarily focused on the theoretical analysis of Relativistic Generative Adversarial Networks (RGANs) and their objective function. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses statistical divergences and their variants, which falls under the sub-category cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper applies RGANs to image generation, which falls under the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the performance of RGANs, which is relevant to the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
